        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix approval runtime gateway calls",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes local agent approval gateway calls so approval request/wait clients identify themselves with the approval runtime token.\n\n## Root cause\n\n`exec.approval.request` and `exec.approval.waitDecision` are backend gateway calls from the local agent path, but the gateway tool client was not forwarding the approval runtime token. That made approved async command completions fail the runtime authorization path in local/web UI flows.\n\n## Changes\n\n- forwards the approval runtime token for local approval request/wait gateway tool calls\n- keeps gateway URL overrides unchanged so remote/explicit gateway calls do not receive the local runtime token\n- passes the token through the lower-level gateway client options\n- adds focused regression coverage for both layers\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\nfnm exec --using 22.21.0 pnpm vitest run src/agents/tools/gateway.test.ts src/gateway/call.test.ts\n```\n\nResult: 5 test files passed, 285 tests passed.\n",
